## Detailed Comparison Timeline

### Era 1: Physical Servers (1990s)
```
[Single Application] 
        |
        v
[Physical Server Hardware]
        |
        v
[Operating System]
        |
        v
[Application + Dependencies]
```
**Issues:**
- Resource waste
- Difficult to scale
- High maintenance costs

### Era 2: Virtual Machines (2000s)
```
[VM1] [VM2] [VM3] [VM4]
  |    |    |    |
  v    v    v    v
[Guest OS] [Guest OS] [Guest OS] [Guest OS]
  |    |    |    |
  v    v    v    v
[App1] [App2] [App3] [App4]
        |
        v
[Hypervisor]
        |
        v
[Host OS + Physical Server]
```
**Benefits:**
- Better resource utilization
- Application isolation
- Easier backup and recovery

**Issues:**
- Heavy resource usage (each VM has full OS)
- Slow startup times
- License costs for multiple OS instances

### Era 3: Containers (Present - Docker)
```
[Container1] [Container2] [Container3] [Container4]
      |          |          |          |
      v          v          v          v
   [App1]     [App2]     [App3]     [App4]
+ Dependencies + Dependencies + Dependencies + Dependencies
      |          |          |          |
      +----------+----------+----------+
                        |
                        v
                [Docker Engine]
                        |
                        v
                [Host OS + Physical Server]
```

