## Deployment Flow Comparison

### Traditional Deployment Flow:
```
Developer -> Code -> Manual Testing -> Manual Build -> 
Manual Deployment -> Server Configuration -> Application Running
Time: Hours to Days
```

### Docker Deployment Flow:
```
Developer -> Code -> Automated Testing -> Docker Build -> 
Container Push -> Automated Deployment -> Application Running
Time: Minutes
```

## Benefits Evolution Matrix

| Aspect | Physical Servers | Virtual Machines | Docker Containers |
|--------|------------------|------------------|------------------|
| **Resource Usage** | Very High | High | Low |
| **Startup Time** | Minutes | Minutes | Seconds |
| **Portability** | None | Limited | Full |
| **Isolation** | None | Full | Good |
| **Density** | 1 app/server | 5-10 apps/server | 20-100 apps/server |
| **Consistency** | Poor | Good | Excellent |
| **Scalability** | Manual | Semi-auto | Automatic |

